Healthcare Payer Payment Rate

Overview

This app visualizes the distribution and relationships between various healthcare features and predicts potential Payer Payment Rates using an H2O model. Once the Payer Payment Rate is predicted, users can perform further in-depth analysis on the predicted data. It leverages advanced analytics and data science techniques to improve decision-making, streamline processes, and enhance the overall efficiency of healthcare payer payment operations.

Input

Users provide:

  • + Patient data, which can be filtered by Gender, Payment Class, Ethnicity, and Category.
  • + Selected features for training the predictive model.
  • + A custom dataset for model validation and prediction.

Output

The app delivers:

  • + Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) of the selected features with meaningful visualizations.
  • + Training metrics of the model trained using chosen features.
  • + Model validation results for the trained model.
  • + Predicted Payer Payment Rates as a percentage of total claim cost covered, aiding reimbursement optimization.
  • + Comprehensive analysis of predicted data, including patient demographics, insurance details, hospital encounters, and diagnostic tests.

Benefits

  • + Optimize reimbursement strategies and improve revenue cycle management.
  • + Gain deeper insights into payment patterns across different patient demographics and service categories.
  • + Streamline payment operations and reduce manual processing efforts.
  • + Make data-driven decisions to enhance financial performance and operational efficiency.
